body:
**Bug Description**
Verilator does not support default values for struct-type parameters in interface/module declarations, even when using aggregate assignment patterns or references to other struct parameters. 

Verilator Version: latest main
Platform: Linux
SystemVerilog Standard: IEEE 1800-2023

**Error Message**
``
%Error: ../tb/axis_if.sv:8:20: Expecting expression to be constant, but can't convert a CONSPACKUORSTRUCT to constant.
``

According to Section 6.20.2 Value Parameters:

> A parameter can also be declared as an aggregate type, such as an unpacked array or an unpacked structure. An aggregate parameter shall be assigned to or overridden as a whole; individual members of an aggregate parameter may not be assigned or overridden separately.


> A value parameter (parameter, localparam, or specparam) can only be set to an expression of literals, value parameters or local parameters, genvars, enumerated names, or a constant function of these. Package references are allowed.


**Testcases**
Setting the struct via an aggregate assignment pattern directly:
```
typedef struct {
    int test;
} axis_cfg_t;

interface axi_stream_if #(
    axis_cfg_t x = '{test: 1}  // Should be legal per IEEE 1800-2023 6.20.3
) (
    input logic clk,
    input logic arstn
);
endinterface

module tb_top;
    logic clk, arstn;
    axi_stream_if axis_if(clk, arstn);  // Should use default value
endmodule
```

Or setting the parameter indirectly via another parameter
```
typedef struct {
    int test;
} axis_cfg_t;

parameter axis_cfg_t default_cfg = '{test: 1};

interface axi_stream_if #(
    axis_cfg_t x = default_cfg  // Should be legal per IEEE 1800-2023 6.20.1
) (
    input logic clk,
    input logic arstn
);
endinterface

module tb_top;
    logic clk, arstn;
    axi_stream_if axis_if(clk, arstn);  // Should use default_cfg value
endmodule
```

